President Barack Obama has announced Jennifer Yeager Kaplan as the new Director of the President's Commission on White House Fellowships. Kaplan, who currently serves as Vice President for Corporate Engagement and Program Officer for the 10,000 Small Businesses Initiative at Goldman Sachs, has a strong background in leadership and experience in various roles within the White House. She previously worked as Deputy Director of the White House Council on Women and Girls and as Special Assistant to the Director in the Office of Public Engagement. Kaplan also held positions in the Obama-Biden Transition Project and worked as a finance director for Obama for America and Hopefund. She obtained a B.S. in Business Administration from The University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. President Obama expressed his confidence in Kaplan's qualifications and looks forward to working with her in the future.